value.description: An array of data items that the sortable component will render.

onValueChange.description:
An optional callback function that is called when the order of the data items changes.
It receives the new array of items as its argument.

onMove.description:
An optional callback function that is called when an item is moved.
It receives an event object with `activeIndex` and `overIndex` properties, representing the original and new positions of the moved item.
This will override the default behavior of updating the order of the data items.

collisionDetection.description: A collision detection strategy that will be used to determine the closest sortable item.

modifiers.description: An array of modifiers that will be used to modify the behavior of the sortable component.

strategy.description: A sorting strategy that will be used to determine the new order of the data items.

orientation.description: Specifies the axis for the drag-and-drop operation. It can be "vertical", "horizontal", or "both".

overlay.description:
An optional React node that is rendered on top of the sortable component.
It can be used to display additional information or controls.

value.description: The unique identifier of the item.

asTrigger.description: Specifies whether the item should act as a trigger for the drag-and-drop action.

asChild.description: Merges the item's props into its immediate child.
